Get Expert Support for Service Cloud Voice

Get help with Voice directly from the experts. If you need assistance, find out whether it’s best to contact Salesforce Support or your telephony provider.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise and Unlimited Editions, Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, Government Cloud as an add-on license.

When to Contact Salesforce Support

* All Service Cloud Voice customers can contact Salesforce Customer Support about issues related to Salesforce functionality.
* Salesforce Standard support is included with Service Cloud Voice. Salesforce Premier, Premier Plus, and Signature/Priority support plans are also available.

When to Contact Your Telephony Provider

Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect
Contact your telephony provider’s support team about issues related to their service. For issues related to Salesforce features, contact Salesforce Support.

TOPIC	CONTACT SALESFORCE	CONTACT YOUR TELEPHONY PROVIDER
* Billing related to your telephony service
* Call quality
* Call recording
* Call transcription
* Contact center setup
* IVR configuration, data fetching, and call routing
* Lightning Service Console
* Omni-Channel and Omni Supervisor
* Phone number availability, provisioning, and porting
* Presence syncing
* Salesforce Einstein services
* Salesforce reporting and analytics
* Single sign-on
* Telephony limits—for example, the maximum number of concurrent calls or phone numbers per instance

Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect
Contact AWS Support about issues related to their service. For issues related to Salesforce features, contact Salesforce Customer Support.

TOPIC	CONTACT SALESFORCE	CONTACT AWS
* Billing
* Call quality
* Call recording
* Call transcription
* Contact center setup
* Lightning Service Console
* Omni-Channel and Omni Supervisor
* Phone number availability, provisioning, and porting
* Presence syncing
* Salesforce-provided contact flows
* Salesforce-provided Lambda functions
* Salesforce Einstein services
* Salesforce reporting and analytics
* Single sign-on
* Telephony limits—for example, the maximum number of concurrent calls or phone numbers per instance
title: Service Cloud Voice Support and Contact Information
